erved in parvalbumin-positive fast-spiking interneurons (PVINs) in Scn1a+/- mice during early development has normalized by postnatal day 35. This work suggests that a transient impairment of PVINs contributes to epilepsy onset, but is not the mechanism of ongoing, chronic epilepsy in Dravet syndrome.",
